  "prompt": "Where can I get free singing lessons via Skype?",
  "response": "There are several options where you can find free singing lessons via Skype or other video conferencing platforms:\n\n1. **YouTube**: Many vocal coaches share free lessons on their channels. You can find tutorials that cover various aspects of singing, which you can then apply in one-on-one sessions if you find a coach willing to offer free lessons.\n\n2. **Social Media**: Platforms like Instagram and Facebook often have vocal coaches who host free live sessions or offer free trials of their services. Look for hashtags like #singinglessons or #vocalcoaching.\n\n3. **Online Communities**: Websites like Reddit have communities (subreddits) such as r/Singing, where you can connect with fellow aspiring singers. You might find someone willing to practice with you over Skype.\n\n4. **Udemy or Skillshare**: Occasionally, you can find free courses on singing on these platforms. While these are not direct lessons, they can provide useful resources to help you learn.\n\n5. **Vocal Coaches Offering Free Trials**: Some vocal coaches offer free trial lessons. You can search for coaches who are willing to conduct a session via Skype, and you may find someone willing to provide a free introductory lesson.\n\n6. **Local Music Schools**: Contact local music schools or instructors. Some may offer free or donation-based introductory lessons or workshops online.\n\n7. **University Programs**: Reach out to music departments at local colleges or universities. Students often need practice teaching and may offer lessons for free or at a reduced rate.\n\nMake sure to research and verify the credentials of any instructor you consider, even for free services. Happy singing!",
